cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper focuses on generating waveforms for speech synthesis, which falls under the domain of sound processing. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper introduces a new text-to-wave neural architecture for speech synthesis, which involves natural language processing. 
- cs.LG (Learning): The paper proposes a new solution for parallel wave generation by distilling a Gaussian inverse autoregressive flow from the autoregressive WaveNet, which involves machine learning techniques. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses an end-to-end model for text-to-speech synthesis, which involves system design and control. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper involves the use of neural networks and machine learning techniques for speech synthesis, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence.
